# What is this? Read the .gitlabels README:
#   <https://github.com/elliottcable/.gitlabels>
#
# Only one tag from each family is required; i.e. (re) and (refactor) are identical; and (puRe) implies (re)

# ## Core (at least one of these should apply to every commit)
- (new feat) new functionality or content
  - (feat feature) entirely new (large) feature; for landing comprehensive additions (almost always paired with (!!))
- (re refactor) subtle improvement; no behavioural change visible to consumers, unless paired with (API)/(BRK)
  - (pure pure-refactor) an explicitly-guaranteed-non-observable refactor (only when typesystem-validated.)
- (fix) fixes a bug or problem

# ## Importance markers
- (- minor) unimportant / safe to skim past. typos, auto-reformats, mechanical, etc
  - (typo) typofix
- (!!) major / widespread / "landing a huge refactor"
- (API) public contract / API surface change
  - (BRK) breaking change (almost always paired with (!!))

# ## Authorship
- (AIa AI-assisted) partially-LLM-authored commit (e.g. some content was generated by an AI, then massaged by the committing human)
  - (AI) LLM-authored commit; mandatory on every AI-created commit

# ## Behavioural impact
- (test e2e) does *not* modify any implementation code, in any way; test-suite only
- (noop) as (tests), except touches no test code either
  - (style fmt) *only* alignment/spacing/formatting of code or documentation
  - (doc) *only* commentary/documentation (exclusive of actual *executed* code)
    - (dsn) edits to design-work documents: DESIGN/KNOBS/TODO, Research/ notes & plans, etc
  - (meta tool tooling) *only* meta-project changes, not affecting runtime behaviour (config, packaging, CI, gitignore)
    - (conf) tool/project-configuration
    - (dep) dependency management
      - (up) bumping a dependency / tool version (often paired with (dep))


# ## Functionality
# Reminder: (don't dupe filenames / crates / modules; only for cross-cutting concerns.)
- (sec security) anything focused on security-impact
- (ana analysis) the, well, analyzer components (static analysis engine)
- (MLm ML-model) LLM-behaviour-tweaking (e.g. AGENTS.md, skills, priming-prompts)

# (crate-named strays in the spike history — analysis/plan/fold/hostsim/oracle/core —
#  predate this file; prefer the cross-cutting labels above)

# ## Other
- (rm) removal of 'something' that isn't just a code-deletion (often paired: (rm dep))
- (typ types) typechecking changes *in the host language*, i.e. Rust type-structure changes (see (ana) for in-language typechecking)
- (mrg merge) merge bookkeeping

# ## Historical
# (strays in the project-history that "just" refer to the crate/component/file are LLM-artifacts; do not use)
- (plan)
- (fold)
- (hostsim)
- (oracle)
- (core)
